"USE MORE QUOTES!" and "Double quote" _every_ expansion, as well as anything that could possibly contain a special character, e.g. "$var", "$@", "${array[@]}", "$(command)". Bash treats everything within 'single quotes' as literal. Learn the difference between ' and " and `. See <http://mywiki.wooledge.org/Arguments>, <http://wiki.bash-hackers.org/syntax/words>, <http://mywiki.wooledge.org/Quotes> and <http://mywiki.wooledge.org/Ba
